Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Stopped by this bar since they had Brandt wheat beer on tap. The bartender was very nice and we enjoyed talking to him. I recommend this place for sure.

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: First time in town, hungover hungry and sleep deprived. Cafe De Zeeneeuw was a nice place to get out of the craziness and relax with good 80's mix. Nice dive bar. Okay now that I'm drunk and had a moment to recharge I'm gonna head back out! Cheers!

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Lovely little find. Quiet little pub. Reasonably priced and family feel in there. Random but amazing decor. Had a chat with the female behind the bar, very friendly and cheerful. It was Christmas we were over here and the locals were brilliantly friendly and welcoming.

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Quiet little pub - I guess it was their off time. I enjoyed a drink and a conversation with the owner. You gotta love these long-standing family businesses.

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Awesome little bar . Bar man was amazing we talked about football for ages . Really good atmosphere.  The bar has old football shirts stuck to the roof and coasters with written messages on . Definitely worth going for a beer and a chat .  P.s (And yes ajax vs liverpool would have been a better CL final )

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Great little pub/cafe with some of the friendliest staff in Amsterdam. Beer mats can be signed and placed onto the walls so some fun times searching for your old beer mats and reading others. Overall this is probably my favourite place to drink and if I lived there it would be my local

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: WE LOVE SYLVIA! Zeemeeuw is a sweet little bar tucked in a corner of the Red Light district. It‚Äôs only bar tender is the sweetest woman I‚Äôve ever met. The drinks are well priced and the music is good! The seating is ample for the crowd. My group of 6 sat comfortably and kept coming back!

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Great place for beer, the owner is awesome to talk

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Sylvia, the bartender, is amazing! She is very caring and friendly. Came into town for 5 days and came back to visit her a second time before we left. Highly recommend if you enjoy small and intimate setting that offers a fun environment.

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: Relaxed, welcoming vibe. The bartender gets a little grumpy when overwhelmed but is a sweetheart really. Far enough from the main attractions of the red light district not to get completely overwhelmed with patrons on a weekend night and drinks are average in price.

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: From N.ireland came in February,19 back again in August,19 for birthday treat. Totally amazing bar, friendly, homely and excellent staff.. make you feel so welcome, and made the birthday night exceptional.. üëç thank you silva for treats made Ciara‚Äôs night so special! Would recommend this bar!!

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: For the first time in Amsterdam, and Marco made us feel just like at home, DO come here if you want some lovely sarcastic comebacks, and real cool bartending. I really enjoyed myself 2/2 would definitely come back, cheers!

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: This is a small dive type bar just on the outskirts of the red light district in Amsterdam. If you are a soccer fan you will be pleased with the decor, as the cieling is completely covered with a variety of soccer jerseys. There also other ‚Ä¶

Review Text: The waitress was not very friendly. We asked for a cappucino and she replied: we have coffee,if u want you add the milk! We also asked for a Chocomel and she replied: this is a bar,not a coffee place! U can say things but u have to be more gentle and educated!!

Name: Cafe De Zeemeeuw
Review Text: cozy and warm escape from the winter. extremely nice bar stools that heated me up instantly. pleasantly touch by the various groups of people coming in and out. had the good stuff..!!1!
